title: How do I know whether my phone is using its mobile data connection or a Wi-Fi connection to access the Internet?
answer: When a Wi-Fi connection is set up, the Wi-Fi connection is used with precedence over the mobile data connection. If ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=112830) is displayed on the upper right corner of your phone, you are using a Wi-Fi connection to access the Internet.
